the%20recovery%20by%20pushing%20up%20long-term%20interest%20rates.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIndustrial%20warehouses%2C%20a%20star%20of%20the%20sector%2C%20is%20poised%20to%20stand%20out%20in%202025.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20commercial%20property%20sector%20has%20had%20a%20bruising%20few%20years%20as%20rising%20interest%20rates%20pushed%20down%20values%2C%20complicated%20refinancing%20deals%20for%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20expiring%20mortgages%2C%20and%20stymied%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20office%20market%2C%20the%20situation%20was%20even%20more%20severe%20as%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20square%20feet%20of%20space%20across%20the%20nation%20face%20accelerated%20obsolescence.%20Employees%20have%20embraced%20hybrid%20and%20remote%20work%20as%20a%20permanent%20offshoot%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20sapping%20demand%20for%20lesser%20quality%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20months%2C%20however%2C%20the%20industry%20has%20felt%20relief%20from%20three%20successive%20rate%20cuts%20by%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20that%20have%20shaved%20a%20percentage%20point%20off%20the%20fed%20funds%20rate%20%E2%80%94%20a%20benchmark%20for%20short-term%20lending%20rates.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-federal-reserve-final-decision-powell-trump-inflation-2024-12%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Fed%2520cuts%2520interest%2520rates%2Cfinal%2520decision%2520of%2520the%2520year%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520Federal%2520Reserve%2520cut%2520interest%2Crate%2520cut%2520of%2520the%2520year.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMore%20cuts%20are%20expected%20in%202025%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Resilient%20economic%20growth%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20propelled%20demand%20for%20commercial%20space%2C%20including%20apartments%2C%20warehouses%2C%20retail%20stores%2C%20and%20hotel%20rooms.%20Some%20developers%20have%20even%20grown%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foffice-construction-demand-upcoming-shortage-real-estate-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebullish%20on%20top-tier%20office%20projects%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20tenants%20flock%20to%20high%20end%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202025%2C%20commercial%20real%20estate%20experts%20have%20signaled%20cautious%20optimism%20that%20the%20sector's%20rebound%20will%20continue%2C%20while%20also%20highlighting%20the%20challenges%20that%20could%20stymie%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20three%20trends%20for%20the%20industry%20to%20watch%20in%202025%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a13674fb-483d-4c07-9eae-d22f0a8b6da1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhile%20the%20Fed%20has%20cut%20rates%2C%20relief%20hasn't%20arrived%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20loans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20roughly%20%244.7%20trillion%20of%20total%20outstanding%20commercial%20real%20estate%20debt%2C%20about%20two-thirds%20is%20tied%20to%20long-term%20interest%20rates%20benchmarked%20against%20the%2010-year%20Treasury%20yield%2C%20according%20to%20an%20estimate%20by%20the%20Mortgage%20Bankers%20Association.%20After%20dipping%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20long-term%20interest%20rates%20have%20jumped%20back%20up%20to%20the%20mid-4%25%20range%2C%20close%20to%20where%20rates%20were%20before%20the%20Fed%20began%20cutting%20and%20far%20higher%20than%20where%20the%2010-year%20was%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%2010-year%20Treasury%20rate%20dipped%20below%20half%20a%20percentage%20point%20in%202020%2C%20its%20lowest%20level%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202025%2C%20observers%20expect%20long-term%20rates%20to%20hold%20steady%2C%20even%20if%20the%20Fed%20continues%20to%20trim%20short-term%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%2010-year%20Treasury%20yield%2C%20that's%20really%20driven%20less%20now%20by%20anticipation%20of%20what%20the%20Fed%20might%20do%20and%20more%20by%20long-term%20expectations%20about%20economic%20growth%20and%20inflation%20and%20federal%20budget%20deficits%2C%26quot%3B%20Jamie%20Woodwell%2C%20the%20MBA's%20head%20of%20commercial%20real%20estate%20research%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20could%20continue%20to%20complicate%20commercial%20real%20estate%20sales%20and%20refinancing%20deals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20MBA%20projects%20that%20%24570%20billion%20of%20commercial%20real%20estate%20loans%20will%20mature%20in%202025%2C%20with%20banks%20holding%20about%2038%25%20of%20the%20overall%20inventory%20of%20outstanding%20debt%20in%20the%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETomasz%20Piskorski%20a%20professor%20of%20real%20estate%20at%20Columbia%20Business%20School%2C%20said%20that%2014%25%20of%20commercial%20loans%20overall%20are%20tied%20to%20distressed%20assets%20that%20are%20now%20worth%20less%20than%20their%20debt%20and%20that%2043%25%20of%20commercial%20real%20estate%20loans%20%26quot%3Bmay%20face%20significant%20cash%20flow%20and%20refinancing%20issues.%26quot%3B%20He%20has%20warned%20there%20could%20be%20tens%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20potential%20losses%20for%20the%20banking%20sector%20and%20other%20lenders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20estate%20services%20giant%20CBRE%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20forecast%20a%20modest%207.5%25%20increase%20in%20investment%20sales%20activity%2C%20predicting%20about%20%24410%20billion%20of%20transactions%20in%202025.%20More%20sales%20would%20help%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20discover%20asset%20pricing%20and%20is%20considered%20a%20positive%20sign%20for%20a%20market%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERichard%20Barkham%2C%20CBRE's%20chief%20economic%20economist%2C%20warned%20of%20lingering%20higher%20long-term%20interest%20rates%20that%20could%20dampen%20the%20rebound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20the%20next%20four%20or%20five%20years%20we're%20likely%20to%20get%20upside%20shocks%20in%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20Barkham%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20points%20to%20an%20era%20of%20interest%20rates%20higher%20for%20longer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a8c7e77a-430a-449a-9de3-13febe630df2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIncoming%20Trump%20administration%20has%20generated%20optimism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump's%20campaign%20promises%20to%20enact%20tariffs%20on%20foreign%20goods%2C%20pressure%20the%20Fed%20for%20lower%20short%20term%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20deport%20undocumented%20immigrants%20from%20the%20labor%20supply%20could%20spur%20inflation%2C%20reigniting%20problems%20in%20the%20commercial%20real%20estate%20financing%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20the%20industry%20has%20been%20largely%20positive%20on%20the%20incoming%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20%26quot%3Bexpect%20better%20tax%20issues%2C%20they%20expect%20less%20regulation%2C%20they%20expect%20some%20real%20estate%20specific%20stuff%20like%20opportunity%20zones%20will%20get%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20boost%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jim%20Costello%2C%20the%20co-head%20of%20real%20assets%20research%20at%20the%20data%20firm%20MSCI%2C%20referencing%20the%20opportunity%20zone%20program%20from%20President%20Trump's%20first%20term%20in%20office.%20Opportunity%20zones%20allowed%20real%20estate%20investors%20the%20chance%20to%20defer%20and%20avoid%20capital%20gains%20taxes%20if%20they%20reinvested%20investment%20proceeds%20in%20property%20projects%20in%20designated%20zones%20around%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Trump%20has%20also%20sought%20to%20hire%20real%20estate%20executives%20in%20his%20administration%2C%20meaning%20that%20top%20officials%20could%20have%20an%20familiarity%20with%20the%20real%20estate%20business%20and%20its%20priorities.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhoward-lutnick-real-estate-newmark-commerce-trump-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHoward%20Lutnick%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20Wall%20Street%20billionaire%20who%20is%20also%20chairman%20of%20the%20large%20commercial%20real%20estate%20services%20firm%20Newmark%20Group%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20has%20been%20picked%20by%20Trump%20to%20lead%20the%20Commerce%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2218ccdff7-b56f-4014-8822-a70fd12b1b98%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfter%20a%20rocky%202024%2C%20industrial%20is%20still%20a%20darling%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIndustrial%20warehouse%20space%20boomed%20during%20the%20pandemic%20as%20American%20shoppers%20migrated%20online%2C%20boosting%20the%20need%20for%20logistics%20spaces%20that%20served%20e-commerce%20and%20also%20to%20onshore%20storage%20for%20a%20disrupted%20global%20supply%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20record%20total%20of%20roughly%20a%20billion%20square%20feet%20of%20industrial%20space%20was%20absorbed%20on%20balance%20by%20occupiers%20in%202022%20and%202023%2C%20according%20to%20Craig%20Meyer%2C%20president%20of%20JLL's%20industrial%20leasing%20group%20in%20the%20Americas.%20That%20activity%20was%20enough%20to%20fill%20a%20vast%20pipeline%20of%20new%20space%20that%20was%20being%20added%20to%20the%20market.%20In%202022%20and%202023%2C%201.1%20billion%20square%20feet%20of%20new%20industrial%20space%20was%20delivered%2C%20according%20to%20JLL%20%E2%80%94%20also%20a%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20however%2C%20demand%20could%20no%20longer%20keep%20pace%20with%20surging%20supply%20%E2%80%93%20stalling%20rental%20growth%20and%20pushing%20up%20vacancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20375%20million%20square%20feet%20of%20new%20space%20was%20added%20to%20the%20industrial%20market%20in%202024%20%E2%80%93%20the%20third%20highest%20year%20on%20record%20after%202022%20and%202023.%20But%20only%20about%20111.3%20million%20square%20feet%20of%20space%20has%20been%20absorbed%20on%20net%2C%20the%20lowest%20year%20of%20absorption%20in%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%20Vacancy%20has%20jumped%20to%206.8%25%20from%204.9%25%20a%20year%20ago.%20In%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%202022%2C%20vacancy%20had%20fallen%20as%20low%20as%203.3%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeyer%20said%20that%20the%20first%20half%20of%202024%20was%20the%20nadir%20of%20the%20dip%20and%20expects%20a%20resurgent%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20a%20contentious%20election%20coming%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Meyer%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20were%20uncertain%20where%20interest%20rates%20were%20going.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202025%2C%20Meyer%20and%20other%20experts%2C%20including%20Barkham%2C%20CBRE's%20economist%2C%20see%20a%20strengthening%20industrial%20market%20as%20new%20supply%20dwindles%20and%20demand%20picks%20back%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20sectors%20that%20are%20big%20and%20improving%20and%20likely%20to%20lead%20investor%20interest%20are%20multifamily%20and%20industrial%2C%26quot%3B%20Barkham%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20268.9%20million%20square%20feet%20of%20industrial%20space%20is%20presently%20under%20construction%2C%20according%20to%20JLL%2C%20the%20smallest%20pipeline%20since%202019.%20E-commerce%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20drivers%20of%20warehouse%20demand%2C%20continues%20to%20grow.%20According%20to%20CBRE%2C%20online%20sales%20are%20expected%20to%20absorb%2030%25%20of%20consumer%20spending%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20decade%2C%20up%20from%2023%25%20today%2C%20adding%20tailwinds%20to%20the%20segment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommercial-real-estate-office-interest-rates-risks-industrial-trump-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735117201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67659bb05cddac6581d73c95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommercial-real-estate-office-interest-rates-risks-industrial-trump-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Commercial%20real%20estate%20has%20been%20battered%20by%20higher%20rates.%20A%20steady%20economy%2C%20falling%20rates%2C%20and%20new%20president%20could%20lead%20to%20an%20upswing%20in%202025.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dgeiger%40businessinsider.com%20(Daniel%20Geiger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommercial-rea